    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The capacity to form or the state of forming mental images or ideas of people, objects, and situations that are not truly present to the senses, including both remembered and constructed ideas and images. In modern philosophy, imagination is the power or capacity by which the mind integrates sensory data in the process of perception.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
